The paper deals with the decidability of equivalence of quantum finite automata, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The use of quantum mechanics in the automata makes it relevant to quantum computing (cs.QL). The paper also involves complexity analysis of algorithms, which falls under computational complexity (cs.CC). The concept of states in automata theory is related to data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves mathematical proofs and reasoning, which is related to logic in computer science (cs.LO).
